    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_Setup_RestorePermissions",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to restore permissions for a specific database object. It retrieves permission details from a temporary table "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "#aspnet_Permissions",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and executes dynamic SQL commands to apply these permissions to the specified object. The procedure uses a cursor to iterate over the permissions associated with the object and constructs SQL commands to grant or deny permissions to specified users or roles."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity of this procedure is considered medium due to the use of dynamic SQL and cursors. While the logic itself is straightforward, the use of dynamic SQL introduces potential security and performance considerations. Additionally, the procedure relies on a temporary table, which adds a layer of complexity in terms of setup and teardown."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@name",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " (sysname): This parameter specifies the name of the database object (e.g., table, view, stored procedure) for which permissions need to be restored. It is used to filter the permissions in the temporary table "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "#aspnet_Permissions",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
